ğŸ”„ Project Flow (Step by Step)
1. User Entry Point (register.html)
The user opens register.html (your welcome file in web.xml).

This page has a form with fields: name, email, mobile.

When submitted, the form sends a POST request to /register.

2. Servlet Mapping (web.xml)
In web.xml, /register is mapped to RegisterServlet.

So the request goes to RegisterServlet.doPost().

3. RegisterServlet.java
Reads form data using req.getParameter("name"), etc.

Creates a Student object and sets values.

Calls StudentDAO.writeStudent(s) to save the student in the database.

After saving, redirects the user to success.jsp.

4. Student.java (Entity Class)
Annotated with @Entity and @Table(name="students").

Represents the students table in MySQL.

Hibernate uses this class to map Java objects to database rows.

5. StudentDAO.java
Handles database operations using Hibernate.

writeStudent(Student s):

Loads hibernate.cfg.xml.

Opens a Hibernate Session.

Begins a transaction.

Persists the Student object into the students table.

Commits transaction.

getAllStudents():

Opens a Hibernate session.

Runs query from Student (HQL).

Returns a List<Student> with all rows from the table.

6. success.jsp
After registration, user sees confirmation: â€œStudent Registered Successfully!â€

Provides links to go back to registration or view all students.

7. ViewStudentsServlet.java
Mapped to /view in web.xml.

When user clicks â€œView All Studentsâ€, request goes to /view.

Servlet calls StudentDAO.getAllStudents().

Stores the list in req.setAttribute("studentList", lst).

Forwards request to viewStudents.jsp.

8. viewStudents.jsp
Retrieves studentList from request.

Iterates over each Student object.

Displays them in an HTML table (ID, Name, Email, Mobile).

Provides link to register another student.

9. hibernate.cfg.xml
Defines database connection (MySQL dac schema).

Maps com.cdac.Student entity.

Configures Hibernate behavior (update, show_sql).

10. error.html
A fallback page in case registration fails.

Provides link to retry registration.

ğŸ“Š Visual Flow Diagram
Code
